FBIS3-59157 "drweu018_o_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-018 Document Type:Daily Report 27 Jan 1994 CYPRUS Clark Comments on Denktas' Reply, Leaves for Athens NC2601173894 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in Greek 1500 GMT 26 Jan 94 NC2601173894 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Language: Greek Article Type:BFN [Text] In a statement this afternoon before leaving for Athens, Joe Clark, the UN secretary general's special representative in Cyprus, said Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktas did not give the United Nations a satisfactory answer on whether he accepts the confidence-building measures in principle. However, he appeared optimistic, saying that in his opinion, the negotiations are very close to reaching an agreement. Clark said: There is only one very significant step left.
